content.text: CAPE TOWN , March 1 ( Reuters ) - Cricket South Africa have not renewed the contracts of frontline spinner Imran Tahir , and all-rounders JP Duminy and Chris Morris , for the 2019/20 season , the union announced on Friday . Tahir and Duminy are expected to be part of South Africa ´ s World Cup squad in England starting in May , but that could well be their swansongs after being overlooked for central contracts .
